Package: trendfilteringSupp
Type: Package
Title: Optimal one-dimensional data analysis with trend filtering
Version: 1.1.0
URL: https://github.com/capolitsch/trendfilteringSupp
Date: 2021-05-17
Author: Collin A. Politsch [aut,cre]
Maintainer: Collin A. Politsch <collinpolitsch@gmail.com>
Authors@R: 
    person(given = "Collin A.",
           family = "Politsch",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "collinpolitsch@gmail.com")
Description: This package serves as a software supplement to 
             Politsch et al. (2020a) and Politsch et al. (2020b). We provide a 
             variety of statistical tools for one-dimensional data analyses 
             with trend filtering (Tibshirani 2014). This package contains 
             user-friendly functionality for optimizing a trend filtering 
             estimator by cross validation or minimizing Stein's unbiased risk 
             estimate, as well as various bootstrap algorithms for producing 
             variability bands to quantify the uncertainty in the trend 
             filtering estimate.
